{s:4:\"data\";s:527:\"<p>If you are new to the Mac operating system, you may be wondering how to print screen on a Mac. You may have already noticed the lack of a “Print Screen” button on the keyboard. This should not make you feel that the process is complex. By using keyboard shortcuts, you can print screen on [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wplook.com/print-screen-mac/\">How to Print Screen on a Mac &#8211; 7 Different Ways</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wplook.com\">WPlook Themes</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Diana\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12500:\"\n<p>If you are new to the Mac operating system, you may be wondering how to print screen on a Mac. You may have already noticed the lack of a “Print Screen” button on the keyboard. This should not make you feel that the process is complex. By using keyboard shortcuts, you can print screen on a Mac. You can capture specific windows or select an area to capture. What they call “Print Screen” in Windows is known as screenshots or screen capture in Mac. Depending on the screen capture action you need, there are several keyboard combinations to use.</p>\n\n\n\n<a href=\"https://wplook.com/product/themes/business/studio-8-agency-wordpress-theme/?ref=30\" title=\"Studio 8 WordPress Theme\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/studio8-001.jpg\" alt=\"Studio 8 WordPress Theme\"></a>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:34px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can pick one of the methods to capture screens and get used to it for everyday use. So let&#8217;s get started and see what are the 7 different ways to print screen on a Mac.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 1: Capture the entire screen</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard.jpg\" alt=\"Print screen mac, Command + Shift + 3\" class=\"wp-image-19011\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard.jpg 1200w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard-300x138.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard-768x353.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard-1024x470.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-mac-keyboard-600x276.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption> Printscreen on Mac, Command + Shift + 3</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> press keys <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>Shift</strong> +<strong>3</strong> simultaneously.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will save a copy of your screen to the clipboard awaiting other actions. You can repeat the key combination without the “Command” key to save the screenshot as a PNG file on your desktop.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 2: Capture a selected area</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard.jpg\" alt=\"Printscreen on Mac, Command + Shift + 4\" class=\"wp-image-19012\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard.jpg 1200w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard-300x138.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard-768x353.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard-1024x470.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-window-mac-keyboard-600x276.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption> Printscreen on Mac, Command + Shift + 4</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong>: begin by pressing the key combination of <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>Shift</strong> + <strong>4</strong> simultaneously.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: the mouse pointer will turn into a crosshair, use it to select the region you are interested in capturing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong>: the spacebar will let you take a full-screen capture.<br> The selection will be copied to the clipboard. If you press the key combinations without the “Command” key, your selection will be saved to the desktop as a PNG file.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 3: Using the Touch Bar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With a MacBook Pro featuring a touch Bar, you can use the Touch Bar to pick from “Selected Portion,” “Window,” or “Entire Screen” after you have simultaneously pressed the <strong>Command</strong>, <strong>Shift</strong> and <strong>4</strong> keys simultaneously. You can also take screenshots of the Touch Bar display using <strong>Shift</strong> + <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>6&nbsp;</strong>or just simply to touch the Screenshot Icon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac.jpg\" alt=\"Print Screen Touch Bar Mac\" class=\"wp-image-19033\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac.jpg 1384w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac-300x178.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac-768x456.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac-1024x607.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-touch-bar-mac-600x356.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1384px) 100vw, 1384px\" /><figcaption> Print Screen Touch Bar Mac</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 4: Take\n	<g class=\"gr_ gr_3 gr-alert gr_spell gr_inline_cards gr_disable_anim_appear ContextualSpelling ins-del\" id=\"3\" data-gr-id=\"3\">screen shots</g> with grab</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have no time to memorize keyboard shortcuts, you can use <strong>Grab</strong>. This program is pre-installed on all Macs and will assist you in creating screenshots from the menu bar. Grab can let you take time-delayed screenshots in case you want to set the stage before you start.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac.jpg\" alt=\"Take screenshots with Grab\" class=\"wp-image-19020\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac.jpg 1600w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-300x165.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-768x422.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-1024x563.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-600x330.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /><figcaption> Take screenshots with Grab</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong>: launch Grab from the utilities housed within the applications folder. Once launched, its icon will display in your dock, you can also pin this icon for quicker access later.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: you can either use the Capture menu system or the keyboard shortcuts detailed alongside the respective command.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac.jpg\" alt=\"Capture Menu\" class=\"wp-image-19021\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac.jpg 1200w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac-300x86.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac-768x220.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac-1024x293.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-window-mac-600x172.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption> Capture Menu &gt; Window</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 5: Timed screen shots with Grab</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Grab gives you the option to capture screenshots on a Mac of the entire screen, an individual window, or a selection of the window. You can do this with a time delay of ten seconds. This gives you some time to properly position your mouse or open the right window before the shot is taken.<br> Begin by opening Grab, then select “Timed Screenshot” or press the shortcut <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>Shift</strong> + <strong>Z</strong>,&nbsp;note that the mouse cursor will not show on the capture but you can change that in the preferences.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences.jpg\" alt=\"Grab Preferences \" class=\"wp-image-19019\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences.jpg 1200w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences-300x159.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences-768x408.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences-1024x544.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/grab-screenshots-mac-preferences-600x319.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /><figcaption> Grab &gt; Preferences</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 6: Using the preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Preview is well known for its functions like opening photos, PDF and other files on Mac. Print screen on Mac is its other hidden feature you should know about. Open preview then highlights the file in the menu bar; the drop-down menu will give you the option to take the screenshot from where you can select “From window” or “From entire screen.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignnone shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac.jpg\" alt=\"Preview &gt; Take Screenshot &gt; From...\" class=\"wp-image-19022\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac.jpg 1500w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac-300x208.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac-768x534.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac-1024x711.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/printscreen-preview-mac-600x417.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\" /><figcaption> Preview &gt; Take Screenshot &gt; From&#8230;</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Even though the keyboard shortcuts methods are faster, the Preview method allows you to choose where the screenshot ends up. You can make edits of the screenshot using Preview before saving with the desired file name and at the preferred location.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Method 7: Capture selection and save to clipboard</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image shadow\"><img src=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac.jpg\" alt=\"print screen on a Mac\" class=\"wp-image-19013\" srcset=\"https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac.jpg 1200w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac-300x138.jpg 300w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac-768x353.jpg 768w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac-1024x470.jpg 1024w, https://wplook.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/print-screen-on-mac-600x276.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n Printscreen on Mac, Command + Control + Shift + 4\n\n\n\n<p>This method is more advanced but is very useful. It helps you print screen on mac with options like a selected area, opened applications, menu bar, parts of a desktop and anything else.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Option one</strong>: capture selected area and save to clipboard. Press <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>Control</strong> + <strong>Shift</strong> + <strong>4</strong> then drag with the mouse to select and save to clipboard. This will change the mouse cursor to +with pixel coordinates. Once you click and drag selection as desired, it will save the area to the clipboard for use in other apps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Option two</strong>: capture selection and save on desktop.<br> Use the <strong>Command</strong> + <strong>Shift</strong> + <strong>4</strong> keys simultaneously then drag with the mouse to select the desired area. When you release the mouse button, the selected area will save on the desktop as a PNG file if not specified otherwise.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you print screen on a Mac, it will be sent to the clipboard or time-stamped then save on the desktop as a PNG file depending on the method used. You do not need to memorize all these keyboard shortcuts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just one or two that are easiest for you then practice on them and you will find it very easy to print screen on a Mac.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wplook.com/print-screen-mac/\">How to Print Screen on a Mac &#8211; 7 Different Ways</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wplook.com\">WPlook Themes</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wplook/~4/_UAnSuw3XVE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://wplook.com/print-screen-mac/feed/\";s:7:\"attr